On June 19, 2020, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation in honor of Father's Day. The proclamation acknowledges the importance of fathers in preparing children for life and instilling essential values. It recognizes fathers as role models who exemplify hard work, devotion to family, self-confidence, and faith. The proclamation states that involved fathers can help foster self-esteem, success in school, empathy, and positive behavior in their children. It emphasizes that fathers play a critical role in shaping society by raising happy, productive, and responsible adults. The proclamation also mentions that the government provides grant funding to organizations working to strengthen relationships between fathers and children, promote responsible parenting, and help fathers find and keep employment. The proclamation calls upon government officials to display the flag of the United States on all government buildings on Father's Day and encourages state and local governments and the people of the United States to observe Father's Day with appropriate ceremonies.